children.text: The insulation has not been installed in the floor space between the two levels.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3999 Thermal Insulation of Dwellings - Bulk Insulation - Installation Requirements, states in section 5.4.2 that
‘In multi-storey construction, the wall space between ceilings and adjacent floors shall be insulated, see Figure 5.4.2’ .
The wall insulation must be installed in these areas to ensure thermal performance prior to the plaster installation.
